management courses using Open Source and Microsoft tools).  Maintain and
update
course curricula and materials for these courses as new technologies become
available. Participate in on-going course and curriculum development
activities
in the department as a whole. Advise students. Carry out departmental and
University service activities.

An M.S. in Computer Science or closely related discipline from an
accredited
college or university is required, as is the ability to communicate
clearly in
written and spoken English. Demonstrated teaching ability in computer
science
service courses and experience in use of multimedia and web-based
educational
technology would be a plus.

